<codeline><highlight class="normal">###<sp/>Limitations<sp/>and<sp/>future<sp/>technical<sp/>improvement</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">The<sp/>detection<sp/>of<sp/>the<sp/>markers<sp/>is<sp/>thought<sp/>only<sp/>for<sp/>this<sp/>particular<sp/>environment,<sp/>so<sp/>if<sp/>the<sp/>user<sp/>were<sp/>to<sp/>use<sp/>`marker_detect.cpp`<sp/>for<sp/>another<sp/>environment,<sp/>it<sp/>would<sp/>not<sp/>work.<sp/>Therefore,<sp/>a<sp/>possible<sp/>improvement<sp/>could<sp/>be<sp/>to<sp/>implement<sp/>a<sp/>solution<sp/>that<sp/>is<sp/>as<sp/>general<sp/>as<sp/>possible,<sp/>in<sp/>order<sp/>to<sp/>use<sp/>it<sp/>with<sp/>whatever<sp/>environment<sp/>we<sp/>have<sp/>at<sp/>hand.</highlight></codeline>
<codeline></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">Another<sp/>limitation<sp/>is<sp/>the<sp/>robot<sp/>itself,<sp/>given<sp/>that<sp/>the<sp/>author<sp/>opted<sp/>for<sp/>a<sp/>very<sp/>easy<sp/>solution.<sp/>A<sp/>possible<sp/>improvement<sp/>could<sp/>be<sp/>to<sp/>buil<sp/>a<sp/>more<sp/>sophisticated<sp/>robot<sp/>or<sp/>tu<sp/>use<sp/>the<sp/>URDF<sp/>of<sp/>a<sp/>commercial<sp/>robot.</highlight></codeline>
